ce:section.ce:para:
The synthesis of CDs can be achieved by heating ASA in ethanol at 200 °C for 18 h. The resulting CDs can be homogeneously dispersed into various solvents. It is observed that CDs are dispersed homogenously in ethanol and 1 M HCl solution, producing a brown solution and a dark brown solution, respectively (Fig. 1
                        ). Transmission electron microscopy (TEM) and scanning probe microscopy (SPM) were performed to check the morphologies of the prepared CDs. As shown in Fig. 2
                        , CDs show uniform nanoparticles with average sizes of about 3 nm (Fig. 2a) and the height of CDs is approximately 2–4 nm (see Fig. 2b, b1-b3).
